com.stormpath.sdk.servlet.http

Interface UserAgent

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultUserAgent

    public interface UserAgent
    Extraordinarily simple representation of an HTTP User agent that supplies only the features needed by the default filter implementations.
    Since:
    1.0.RC3

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      List<MediaType> getAcceptedMediaTypes() 
      boolean isBrowser()
      Returns true if the user agent is likely a web browser and not a library or command line client.
      boolean isHtmlPreferred()
      Returns true if the user agent prefers HTML (or XHTML) content, false otherwise.
      boolean isJsonPreferred()
      Returns true if the user agent prefers JSON content, false otherwise.

    • Method Detail

      • isBrowser

        boolean isBrowser()
        Returns true if the user agent is likely a web browser and not a library or command line client. This is a best effort evaluation - it does not protect against user agents that spoof the User-Agent header of known browsers.
        Returns:
        true if the user agent is likely a web browser and not a library or command line client.

      • getAcceptedMediaTypes

        List<MediaType> getAcceptedMediaTypes()

      • isHtmlPreferred

        boolean isHtmlPreferred()
        Returns true if the user agent prefers HTML (or XHTML) content, false otherwise. HTML preference in this context is determined by looking at the Accept header and seeing if application/html or application/xhtml+xml are listed first before application/json.
        Returns:
        true if the user agent prefers HTML (or XHTML) content, false otherwise.

      • isJsonPreferred

        boolean isJsonPreferred()
        Returns true if the user agent prefers JSON content, false otherwise. JSON preference in this context is determined by looking at the Accept header and seeing if application/json is listed first before application/html or application/xhtml+xml.
        Returns:
        true if the user agent prefers JSON, false otherwise.
